kdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_7279227\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 28, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yop1718603850178.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yop1718603850178.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yop1718603850178.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tbp1665702926537\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Disabling\n      Database Referential Integrity Temporarily</h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When loading large amounts of data into a database that is prepared for database\n      referential integrity, it is useful to temporarily drop referential integrity and re-create\n      the relationship in the database. Use the Create Script facility (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/gensql</span>)\n      to generate the required scripts.</p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"tbp1665702926537__context_w2201ab1b5b1_w2202ab1b5_w2203ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tbp1665702926537__p_d47219e1_d47220e1_d47221e1\">Before you begin, create or obtain the SQL scripts to drop referential integrity. See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wly1665702737011.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wly1665702737011.html\" title=\"For some database systems, you can have the DBMS (instead of Uniface) manage referential integrity. To do so you need to generate referential integrity scripts and have the database administrator execute those scripts in the target database.\">Generate Referential Integrity Scripts</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"tbp1665702926537__li_d23555e1_d23556e1_d23557e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Configure the connector to enable Uniface referential integrity by adding or removing the relevant connector option. See the connector documentation for your DBMS.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"tbp1665702926537__li_d23558e1_d23559e1_d23560e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Execute the scripts to drop referential integrity constraints\n                  (<span class=\"ph filepath\">*_dropReferentialIntegrity.sql</span>).</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"tbp1665702926537__li_d23561e1_d23562e1_d23563e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Load the data into the tables.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"tbp1665702926537__li_d23564e1_d23565e1_d23566e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Run the script to validate relationship constraints ( (<span class=\"ph filepath\">*_validateReferentialIntegrity.sql</span>).).\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"tbp1665702926537__li_d23567e1_d23568e1_d23569e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Investigate and resolve any reported violations of referential integrity.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"tbp1665702926537__li_d23570e1_d23571e1_d23572e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Execute the script to enforce referential integrity constraints (<span class=\"ph filepath\">*_createReferentialIntegrity.sql</span>).\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wly1665702737011.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Generate Referential Integrity Scripts</a><p>For some database systems, you can have the DBMS (instead of Uniface) manage referential integrity. To do so you need to generate referential integrity scripts and have the database administrator execute those scripts in the target database.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7279227\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7279227\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Disabling Database Referential Integrity Temporarily Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 28, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Disabling Database Referential Integrity Temporarily When loading large amounts of data into a database that is prepared for database referential integrity, it is useful to temporarily drop referential integrity and re-create the relationship in the database. Use the Create Script facility ( /gensql ) to generate the required scripts. Before you begin, create or obtain the SQL scripts to drop referential integrity. See Generate Referential Integrity Scripts . Configure the connector to enable Uniface referential integrity by adding or removing the relevant connector option. See the connector documentation for your DBMS. Execute the scripts to drop referential integrity constraints ( *_dropReferentialIntegrity.sql ). Load the data into the tables. Run the script to validate relationship constraints ( ( *_validateReferentialIntegrity.sql ).). Investigate and resolve any reported violations of referential integrity. Execute the script to enforce referential integrity constraints ( *_createReferentialIntegrity.sql ). Related Links Generate Referential Integrity Scripts For some database systems, you can have the DBMS (instead of Uniface) manage referential integrity. To do so you need to generate referential integrity scripts and have the database administrator execute those scripts in the target database. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}